      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is this GDPR compliant for UK businesses?<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><strong>Yes — and we take this seriously.</strong> Our system operates within UK GDPR guidelines. Before any campaign goes live, we assess the legal basis for contacting your specific database — typically legitimate interests for previously expressed enquiries. We will not proceed with any campaign that doesn't have a clear compliance pathway. If your leads previously enquired about your service, there is almost always a legitimate basis to re-engage them.<div class="gdpr-badge"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 1L3 5v6c0 5.5 3.8 10.7 9 12 5.2-1.3 9-6.5 9-12V5l-9-4z"/></svg>GDPR Compliant Operations</div></div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">We've tried contacting our database before and it didn't work.<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">That's the most common thing we hear — and it's almost always because the approach was either a generic email blast or a manual calling effort that gave up too early. <strong>Our system averages a 40% response rate on lists other methods got under 5% from.</strong> The difference isn't the list. It's the conversation — real, personalised, objection-handling conversations that human teams don't have the capacity to run at scale.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Our leads are really old — some haven't been contacted in over a year.<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><strong>Good.</strong> Some of our best results have come from lists that were 6–18 months cold. People's circumstances change. Budgets free up. Problems that weren't urgent become urgent. Simon's campaign ran on leads that had been sitting for over a year. The leads you wrote off eight months ago might be the most ready-to-buy people in your entire database — they just need someone to start the right conversation.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I know the appointments will actually be qualified?<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Every lead goes through a <strong>real conversation</strong> — not a form fill or a button click. They're asked qualifying questions specific to your offer, their interest is confirmed, and they actively book a specific time. We don't count someone as a booked appointment unless they've been through the full qualification sequence. You can listen to exactly how this sounds in the recordings above — including Andrew, who tried to end the conversation in the first ten seconds and still ended up booked.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">We're not sure we can handle more appointments right now.<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">We hear this a lot — and we get it. That's why <strong>we control the pace.</strong> We don't flood your calendar with 60 appointments in a week if your team can only handle 10. We dial up or dial down the appointment velocity to match your capacity. Some clients start with a controlled pilot of 500 contacts before opening the full list — that's completely fine.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Will leads know they're talking to an AI?<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Listen to the recordings above — leads were booking in without clocking it wasn't a real person. The agent handles real-time objections, timezone corrections, scheduling preferences, and conversational detours naturally. <strong>It sounds like a trained member of your team.</strong> We're transparent about the technology in our compliance framework and follow all applicable regulations around AI disclosure where legally required.</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does it cost and how does pricing work?<span class="faq-arrow"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">We don't publish pricing because it depends on your list size, industry, and campaign structure. <strong>Our model is performance-oriented</strong> — we only win when you win. Book a discovery session and we'll tell you exactly what a campaign would look like for your specific database, what results are realistic, and what it costs. If the numbers don't make sense for you, we'll tell you that directly rather than waste your time.</div></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

